<br>
Coustea's 1976 speech before the UN was actual long and detailed. I use his conclusion becuase is it tightly encapsulates the bottom line.<br>
<br>
I do, whenever possible, post either detailed analysis or links to relevant material. <br>
<br>
I think a browse around my postings on the subject of the inevitable linkages between civilian and military nuclear power would show that I strive to discuss in depth.<br>
<br>
In any event.. What I (and Cousteau) say is not particulary controversial. It is the central fact of regulating nuclear proliferation. That fact is the reason for the IAEA. That fact is what the crisis with North Korea is about. That fact is the basus for the controversy with Iran. <br>
<br>
The dual-usage inevitability is an absolute middle-of-the road position. <br>
<br>
